	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Does the board tap the system's clock? Was the system NTSC in the first place? You probably have a 60hz NTSC unit which does transcode video to 50hz PAL-M, I have an unlicensed replacement PAL transcoder for NTSC Famicom which does this and presumably outputs PAL-I. If thats the case, you can just remove the board as long as it doesn't intercept anything from the main board (as my Famicom does) BTW, does the addon board contain a large DIP IC?

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


