		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I'm going to check all of this tomorrow 'cause that's when I have some free time to open the console again.
<br />
<br />I have strong reasons to believe it was NTSC. And PAL-M, as incredible as it may seem, is not 50Hz, it's 60Hz. Look <a href="http://www.videointerchange.com/pal_secam_conversions.htm#PAL" class="postlink">here</a>.
<br />
<br />Anyway, thanks for checking this out, and I'll sure look into the details you asked soon!

		

		</td>
	</tr>
