	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Ok, I checked a few more things. I couldn't take any pictures because WinXP refused to detect my camcorder through the firewire port (tried for about an hour)...
<br />
<br />But I took a picture from the web and drew exactly where the seven wires that come from the added board are soldered to. It's <a href="http://www.nesstuff.kit.net/pal-m.jpg" class="postlink">here</a>. Please ignore the red arrows, they were meant for the guide where I stole the pic from.
<br />
<br />As it says in the picture, the trace leading to the spot where the yellow wire is connected has been cut. The board usually stays above the rest, on the right (when looking to this picture), and this NES had no shield covering everything. The added board has no large DIP IC.
<br />
<br />The part numbers for PPU and CPU are RP2C02G-0 and RP2A03G. Oh, and now that I looked again there's a sticker on the mainboard saying "NTSC". So yeah, I think it was NTSC.
<br />
<br />Maybe the board can be removed and a wire can reconnect the spots that had the trace cut?

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


